`.\n\n**Query Service API Server**: `/pkg/registry/apis/query/` provides a Kubernetes-style API server:\n- `query.go` implements the REST storage layer with a `Connect()` method that acts as a POST handler for the query endpoint, calling `handleQuery()` which orchestrates the flow\n- `register.go` defines `QueryAPIBuilder` which sets up the API server and registers routes\n- `client/plugin.go` implements `QueryData()` that converts k8s-style requests to backend format and dispatches to plugins\n- `plugins.go` manages plugin registry/discovery for the API\n\n**Aggregator Plugin Handler**: `/pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/query.go` provides `QueryDataHandler()` as an HTTP handler that processes query requests in the aggregator, converting query data requests and dispatching to the plugin client.\n\n**Response Transformation**: \n- `/pkg/expr/query_convert.go` with `ConvertBackendRequestToDataRequest()` converts backend query requests to k8s experimental API format\n- `/pkg/promlib/querydata/response.go` implements response parsing with `parseResponse()` which converts HTTP responses to backend DataResponse format\n\n**Datasource Implementations**: Specific datasources like `/pkg/tsdb/prometheus/prometheus.go` implement the datasource plugin interface by delegating to the promlib service (`/pkg/promlib/library.go`), which uses the custom query execution in `/pkg/promlib/querydata/request.go`'s `Execute()` method.\n\n**Client Middleware**: Query requests flow through middleware in `/pkg/services/pluginsintegration/clientmiddleware/` including caching, metrics, logging, and tracing middleware that enrich the request/response cycle.\n\n**API Types**: `/pkg/apis/query/v0alpha1/query.go` defines `QueryDataRequest` and `QueryDataResponse` types that wrap the backend SDK types with Kubernetes metadata.\n\nThe complete flow: HTTP Request → API Handler → Query Service → Plugin Manager → Backend Plugin Client → Datasource Implementation → Response Parsing → Response Transformation → HTTP Response."
